description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;Head of Nursing Professional Practice and Safety Standards.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced nurse leader to undertake the role of Head of Nursing: Professional Practice &amp; Safety Standards in Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust. One of the largest Trusts in England and rated GOOD by the Care Quality Commission and with a Nursing and Midwifery workforce in excess of 4500 staff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be an experienced and credible nurse leader with the ability to motivate and inspire staff to deliver the highest possible clinical and professional standards. You will be a clinical role model and will be passionate about improvement and patient-centered care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an experienced clinical nursing lead who can passionately and confidently use their fantastic communication skills to engage and collaborate with our senior leaders and nursing colleagues. You will provide professional leadership and specialist expertise within the Trust and work regularly with key stakeholders on a national, regional and local basis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lead the development of the Trust’s strategic approach to provide the nursing and midwifery workforce with evidence based safety standards to ensure that they are able to provide a safe and quality service to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;lead the Trust’s co-ordination and implementation of a range of key projects that run alongside the Trust’s nursing and midwifery education, training and workforce strategies to ensure a safe and productive workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;        &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;direct line management responsibility for specific services including the Tissue Viability Service and Clinical Practice and Safety Standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As part of the Chief Nurse Team the post holder will be an ambassador for the organisation with extensive experience at a senior leadership level. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal enquires please contact: Lisa Grant, Chief Nurse, Leeds Teaching Hospitals: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;lisa.grant5@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 0113 2065835&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; Or &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Helen Christodoulides, Deputy Chief Nurse,  Leeds Teaching Hospitals:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Helen.christodoulides@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 0113 2066021 &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date Sunday 8th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews are expected to take on 25 November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
